HEADWORD: Soulless
<hw>Soul"less</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Being without a
soul, or without greatness or nobleness of mind; mean;
spiritless.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Slave, <qex>souless</qex> villain, dog!</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Soullessly</ent>⟦br⟧
